  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Emergency Ambulance Service - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_emergency_ambulance_service">Emergency Ambulance Service</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_emergency_ambulance_service">Emergency Ambulance Service</xref>
 is the provision of an emergency 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICE</xref>
 to 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 following a call to an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_ambulance_control_room">Ambulance Control Room</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_emergency_ambulance_service">Emergency Ambulance Service</xref>
 and integration within the wider health economy, see the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_association_of_ambulance_chief_executives">Association of Ambulance Chief Executives</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://aace.org.uk" scope="external" format="html">AACE</xref>
.  </p>

